23.74	Digital_recording	Digital recording	In digital recording, digital audio and digital video is directly recorded to a storage device as a stream of discrete numbers, representing the changes in air pressure for audio and chroma and luminance values for video through time, thus making an abstract template for the original sound or moving image.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Zoom_H4n_audio_recording_levels.jpg/220px-Zoom_H4n_audio_recording_levels.jpg
